===Digital streaming===
The series had been available for streaming on [[Netflix]].  The first season was available on [[Hulu]]. Some episodes are available on NBC's web site.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.nbc.com/classic-tv/knight-rider-classic/video Knight Rider]. NBC.com&lt;/ref&gt;

==Spin-offs and sequels==
{{main|Knight Rider}}
These adventures were continued with the [[television film]]s ''[[Knight Rider 2000]]'' and ''[[Knight Rider 2010]]'' and the short-lived ''[[Team Knight Rider]]''. One other television movie, ''[[Knight Rider (2008 film)|Knight Rider]]'', served as a [[television pilot|pilot]] for the short-lived 2008 revived television series ''[[Knight Rider (2008 TV series)|Knight Rider]]''. In 1985, a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] series, ''[[Code of Vengeance]]'', also premiered.

In 1988, Angelo di Marco made a French comic strip based on the series, titled ''K2000'' and published by [[Dargaud]].&lt;ref&gt;https://www.lambiek.net/artists/d/di-marco-angelo.htm&lt;/ref&gt;

==In popular culture==
In 1984, &quot;Hooray for Hollywood&quot;, a two-part episode of ''[[Diff'rent Strokes]]'', David Hasselhoff and KITT (not voiced by William Daniels) appeared when rescuing Arnold Jackson ([[Gary Coleman]]) and Dudley Ramsey ([[Shavar Ross]]) from a near on-set incident while visiting Universal Studios Hollywood.

[[File:A black Pontiac Firebird Trans Am built to mimic KITT from the TV series Knight Rider.jpg|alt=|thumb|A black Pontiac Firebird Trans Am built to mimic [[KITT]] from the TV series ''Knight Rider''.]]
On July 8, 2008, [[Mio GPS|GPS]] manufacturer [[Mio Technology]] announced the release of a Knight Rider-themed GPS unit for a price of $270. The unit has the original Knight Rider logo printed above the display and features the voice of William Daniels.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite press release|publisher=MiTAC Intl. |url=http://www.mio.com/us/mio-technology-press-releases-17833.htm |title=Knight Rider GPS by Mio Brings K.I.T.T. to Every Car |date=July 8, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090316064004/http://mio.com/us/mio-technology-press-releases-17833.htm |archivedate=March 16, 2009 }}&lt;/ref&gt;

In 2012 and 2013, General Electric ran an advertising campaign, &quot;Brilliant Machines&quot;, about the coming generation of General Electric robotic devices. The campaign was built around famous robots from the movies and television, and K.I.T.T. was prominently featured.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MwNIyloRtdo|title=GE&amp;nbsp;â€” Journey|work=YouTube|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}&lt;/ref&gt; One ad, narrated by William Daniels, showed K.I.T.T. in Autocruise mode pacing a GE diesel-electric railroad engine hauling a freight train.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M6tAgUcuNN0|title=Knight Rider KITT and the Locomotive Train GE 2012 TV Commercial|work=YouTube|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}&lt;/ref&gt;

In 2014, [[Fast 'n Loud]] did a two part episode, &quot;Don't Hassle The Hoff&quot;, built around a friend of [[Richard Rawlings]]' desire to own a KITT replicar. Part II features the replicar engaging in a number of ''Knight Rider''-style stunts.&lt;ref&gt;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4325346/&lt;/ref&gt;

In 2015, both David Hasselhoff and KITT (voiced by [[Seth MacFarlane]]) appear in a Comic-Con segment in the unrated version of [[Ted 2]]. Hasselhoff and KITT later paired together again for an [[AT&amp;T]]/[[DirecTV]] advertisement which also featured other film/television personalities such as [[Big Bird]] and the [[Oklahoma Sooners football]] team interspersed with the daily workings of a major city as someone walks around using the service's [[TV Everywhere]] initiative.&lt;ref&gt;[https://www.ispot.tv/ad/AirC/at-and-t-everywhere &quot;AT&amp;T TV Commercial, 'Everywhere'&quot;]. ''iSpot.tv''. Accessed 3 February 2017.&lt;/ref&gt;

In the 2015 [[Kung Fury]] film, the main character Kung Fury has a talking car &quot;Hoff 9000&quot;, voiced by David Hasselhoff. (The 9000 is a reference to [[HAL 9000]], and the Hoff 9000 is unwilling to open the car doors.){{citation needed|date=September 2019}}

In 2018 [[Wal-Mart]] made an ad promoting their new curbside pickup service starring epic Hollywood automobiles. KITT is featured in four shots and has a spoken line.&lt;ref&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=whpJBY5W7xo&lt;/ref&gt;

===Music===
The ''Knight Rider'' theme was sampled in the songs &quot;[[Clock Strikes]]&quot;, &quot;[[Turn It Up (Remix)/Fire It Up|Fire It Up]]&quot;, and &quot;[[Mundian to Bach Ke]]&quot;,&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/playback/2004/winter/hiphopsoul2.aspx|title=the best in hip hop/soul|work=www.ascap.com|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}&lt;/ref&gt; and was also featured as Ted's [[ringtone]] in John's phone in the 2012 comedy film ''[[Ted (film)|Ted]]''.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.moviehabit.com/review.php?story=ted_f912|title=Movie Habit.com&amp;nbsp;â€” Review of ''Ted'' (*1/2)|publisher=|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}&lt;/ref&gt;

